Class Pipeline<I extends Organism>

  • java.lang.Object
    • objenome.solver.evolve.Pipeline<I>

    public class Pipeline<I extends Organism>
extends java.lang.Object
implements PopulationProcess<I>
    A Pipeline applies a sequence of population processes Pipelines are themselves population processes.

    • Method Detail

      • process

        public Population<I> process(Population<I> population)
        Processes all the components of this pipeline in sequence. The provided population is supplied to the first component of the sequence, with each successive component given the population returned by the previous component.
        Specified by:
        process in interface PopulationProcess<I extends Organism>
        Parameters:
        population - the Population to be passed to the first component in the pipeline
        Returns:
        a Population returned by the last component in the pipeline. If this pipeline is empty then the returned Population will be the same Population that was provided as a parameter.

      • add

        public void add(int index,
                PopulationProcess component)
        Inserts the provided Component into this pipeline at the specified index. Any components currently residing at that position, and any subsequent components, are shifted backwards one index position.
        Parameters:
        index - the index at which the given Component is to be inserted. The components are indexed from 0.
        component - the Component to add to this pipeline
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is out of range (index < 0 || index > size())

      • remove

        public boolean remove(PopulationProcess component)
        Removes the first occurrence of the specified Component from this pipeline if it is present. If this pipeline does not contain the component then it is unchanged.
        Parameters:
        component - the Component to be removed from this pipeline, if present
        Returns:
        true if the component was in this pipeline, and false otherwise

      • remove

        public PopulationProcess remove(int index)
        Removes the Component at the specified index in this pipeline. Any subsequent components are shifted forwards one index position. The component that was removed is returned.
        Parameters:
        index - the index of the component to be removed
        Returns:
        the component previously at the specified position
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - if the index is out of range (index < 0 || index > size())
